            <abstract><p>Glad of Smith's good health; hopes he keeps out of aggravating London air. Defeated in Liverpool election "with about 400 single unsolicited votes"; blames the "great animosity" against him on account of the slave trade, suspects it is sometimes conveyed "in the more popular phrase of Church &amp; King". Encloses an address on the matter; his friends insist there were irregularities in the poll but he is fed up of the "violence, abusy, &amp; scrutiny" of elections.</p></abstract>
